name: Crimthann

attributes.attribute: Name of several kings of Ireland

sources: Monaghan, Patricia. The Encyclopedia of Celtic Mythology and Folklore. Checkmark Books, 2008.
text: Named after Christian saint Colum Cille, who was a missionary scholar, several kings in Ireland were also called by the name Crimthann. The Crimthanns were significant figures, and the text does not dive into a specific topic but instead mentions the prominent figures with the name.
